<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
If sg_out is different from sg_in but does not point to a buffer large enough for nents_in elements (or is NULL), the memcpy call will read/write beyond the bounds of the sg_out/sg_in objects. Example: nents_in == 10 but sg_out was allocated/contains space for only 5 struct metal_sg elements (or sg_out == NULL) — memcpy(sg_out, sg_in, 10 * sizeof(struct metal_sg)) will overflow, violating Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

